node.text:
Mass evacuations as fires in #Greece continue to spread. Temperatures recently soared to scary highs of 47 Celsius! 😢

The first video shows people being evacuated on the ferry from the picturesque town of Limni in Evia, which is now burned to the ground. A total catastrophe. Imagine living your life in peace next to the sea, and the next day you have to leave your home, never to see it again. It’s heartbreaking. 

Please share this with your friends and loved ones.

@the_hellenic_initiative have launched a wildfire relief fundraising campaign. 100% of the money collected in this campaign will be allocated to vetted, trusted NGO’s and the firefighters. They’re currently at $54,000 of their $100,000 target 🙏🏽
find the link in @the_hellenic_initiative’s bio if you’d like to help. 🇬🇷

Photos/videos by:
#1: @AlexMaragos
#2: Stavros Dem
#3: VPetsopoulos on Twitter
#4: @kosmaskoumianos

Via @earthfocus
